SIMPLE: timer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Timer
<hw>Tim"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
timekeeper; especially, a watch by which small intervals of time can be
measured; a kind of stop watch. It is used for timing the speed of
horses, machinery, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Internal-combustion Engines)</fld> <def>In electric
ignition, an adjustable device for automatically timing the
spark.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Timesaving</ent>⟦br⟧
